OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1780016591
OL,3,CPrincess of Wales' brother-in-law
OL,4,Copposes public footpath at family home
OL,6,FSubscribe free to our weekly
OL,7,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,8,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,9,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,11,FMatthews, who purchased the 32-room
OL,12,Fproperty in August 2022, objected to
OL,13,Fthe decision, and told the inquiry the
OL,14,Fgate had raised no objections from the
OL,15,Flocal parish council or neighbours.
OL,17,FHe and Pippa live in the #15million
OL,18,F145-acre property with their three
OL,19,Fyoung children.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1780016591
OL,3,CPrincess of Wales' brother-in-law
OL,4,Copposes public footpath at family home
OL,6,FSpeaking at on the first day of the
OL,7,Finquiry on Thursday, Matthews said
OL,8,Fthere was nothing in the conveyancing
OL,9,Fprocess which alerted him to any
OL,10,Fpublic use of the drive when he bought
OL,11,Fthe home.
OL,13,F"There are implications for my family,
OL,14,Fdue to their high public profile,
OL,15,Fwhich means there is a need for a
OL,16,Fhigher level of security than would
OL,17,Fotherwise be the case if the
OL,18,Fcircumstances were different," said
OL,19,FMatthews, whose brother Spencer was a
OL,20,Fcast regular on Made in Chelsea.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31405
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1780016591
OL,3,CPrincess of Wales' brother-in-law
OL,4,Copposes public footpath at family home
OL,6,F"Therefore to improve security for my
OL,7,Ffamily, before we moved in, I arranged
OL,8,Ffor an electric security gate to be
OL,9,Ferected on the drive."
OL,11,FMatthews said the gate is "kept shut"
OL,12,Fexcept on the odd occasion that family
OL,13,For friends may visit, and had been
OL,14,Fstrengthened in 2025 due to a
OL,15,F"continued need to enhance security".
OL,17,FHe also said he had seen "only a
OL,18,Fhandful of people, on maybe two or
OL,19,Fthree occasions, walking along the
OL,20,Fdrive" in the last three-and-a-half
OL,21,Fyears.
OL,26,@yD@ZOU|D@FO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31406
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1780016591
OL,3,CPrincess of Wales' brother-in-law
OL,4,Copposes public footpath at family home
OL,6,FMatthews told the inquiry at Kintbury
OL,7,FCoronation Hall, Hungerford, he had
OL,8,Fspoken to those on the drive each time
OL,9,Fand told them it was not a public
OL,10,Ffootpath and they had agreed with him.
OL,12,FA spokesperson for Matthews and his
OL,13,Ffamily said he had the right to
OL,14,F"create a safe environment on his
OL,15,Fprivate property, for his young
OL,16,Fchildren playing outside, away from
OL,17,Fforeseeable risks through uncontrolled
OL,18,Ftrespassers and traffic".
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31407
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1780016591
OL,3,CPrincess of Wales' brother-in-law
OL,4,Copposes public footpath at family home
OL,6,F"For as long as records exist, there
OL,7,Fhas never been a footpath/public right
OL,8,Fof way on the land currently under
OL,9,Fdiscussion," the spokesperson said.
OL,11,F"For decades past there has always
OL,12,Fbeen signage pointing out this is the
OL,13,Fdriveway to a private property, with
OL,14,Fno public access. There are other
OL,15,Fclearly marked footpaths nearby."
OL,26,@nD@AOUwD@aO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31408
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1780016591
OL,3,CPrincess of Wales' brother-in-law
OL,4,Copposes public footpath at family home
OL,6,FIn a statement, West Berkshire
OL,7,FDistrict Council said the application
OL,8,Fwas based on "the legal principle that
OL,9,Fa public footpath can be deemed to
OL,10,Fexist if it has been enjoyed by the
OL,11,Fpublic for an uninterrupted period of
OL,12,F20 years, without force, secrecy or
OL,13,Fpermission", or had been dedicated by
OL,14,Fa landowner in the past.
OL,16,FDavid Hill, the estate manager for
OL,17,FBarton Court between 2016 and 2022,
OL,18,Ftold the inquiry on Thursday morning
OL,19,Fhe did not recall regularly
OL,20,Fencountering people on the drive who
OL,21,Fwere being told not to be there.
OL,26,@pD@NOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31409
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1780016591
OL,3,CPrincess of Wales' brother-in-law
OL,4,Copposes public footpath at family home
OL,6,F"Occasionally I would come across
OL,7,Fsomeone who appeared to be lost or
OL,8,Funaware that they should not be there.
OL,9,FIt's hard to estimate but probably one
OL,10,Fperson every two-to-three months
OL,11,Falthough sometimes not as often as
OL,12,Fthat," he said.
OL,14,F"Always individuals, never groups. In
OL,15,Fthose instances, I would ask whether
OL,16,Fthey were lost or whether they needed
OL,17,Fassistance. I would tell them that it
OL,18,Fwas not a public footpath and was a
OL,19,Fprivate drive.
OL,26,@nD@AOUvD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31410
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1780016591
OL,3,CPrincess of Wales' brother-in-law
OL,4,Copposes public footpath at family home
OL,6,F"They would either turn back the way
OL,7,Fthey had come, or if they were close
OL,8,Fto the other end of the route, I might
OL,9,Fallow them to continue."
OL,11,FTrevor Coles, a nearby resident of the
OL,12,Farea, said in a written statement:
OL,13,F"Past proprietors of Barton Court have
OL,14,Falways respected the authenticity and
OL,15,Fvalue of this right of way and it is
OL,16,Fonly since new owners have been in
OL,17,Fresidence that obstructions have
OL,18,Fappeared.
OL,26,@nD@AOUqD@XO]uD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,315,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31411
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1780016591
OL,3,CPrincess of Wales' brother-in-law
OL,4,Copposes public footpath at family home
OL,6,F"Historically, I have absolutely no
OL,7,Frecall of any hindrance being put in
OL,8,Fthe way of locals and ramblers."
OL,10,FIn another written statement, Neal
OL,11,FJames Pike said: "I do not understand
OL,12,Fwhy the present owners are trying to
OL,13,Fclose the use of Mill Lane when it has
OL,14,Fbeen used by the walking public for
OL,15,Fdecades.
OL,17,F"It will interrupt free movement of
OL,18,Fpeople who appreciate the lovely
OL,19,Fvillage of Kintbury and its
OL,20,Fsurrounding countryside."
OL,26,@nD@AOUpD@`O]sD@ROUyD@AOU|D@YO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
